  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-06-27",
    "date": "2007-07-25T19:21:27Z",
    "text": "Enhanced Financial Recovery and Equitable Retirement Treatment Act of 2007 - Imposes surcharges for unpaid criminal monetary penalties and for unpaid balances on money judgments obtained by the United States.\n\nIncreases special assessments on persons convicted of certain criminal offenses against the United States.\n\nEstablishes in the Treasury the Department of Justice Enhanced Financial Recovery Fund to support Department of Justice debt collection activities.\n\nRequires assistant U.S. attorneys to be treated in the same manner as federal law enforcement officers for purposes of federal employee retirement benefit provisions."
  },
